# Language-Specific Style

## Shell (bash/zsh/dash)
- Use `#!/bin/sh` for portable scripts, `#!/bin/bash` only when bash-isms needed
- Quote all variables: `"$var"` not `$var`
- Use `[[ ]]` in bash, `[ ]` in sh
- Prefer `command -v` over `which`

## Python
- Type hints for all function signatures
- f-strings over .format() or %
- dataclasses over plain dicts for structured data
- pathlib over os.path

## C (suckless style)
- Tabs for indentation
- Functions: return type on separate line
- Opening brace on same line for control flow, new line for functions
- No C++ style comments in pure C

## Emacs Lisp
- use-package for package configuration
- lexical-binding in all files
- Prefer built-in functions over external packages
- Hook functions named: `my/<mode>-hook`

## JavaScript/TypeScript
- async/await over .then() chains
- Destructuring for function params when >2 properties
- Arrow functions for callbacks, named functions for exports
- ESM imports, never CommonJS require()
